flyMD Non-Commercial Open Source License (NC 1.0)

Copyright (c) 2024-2025, flyhunterl <flyhunterl@gmail.com>

This English text is an informative translation of the original Chinese license. In the event of any inconsistency or ambiguity, the Chinese version shall prevail.

1. Scope
This software is open source for Non-Commercial use only. You may use, copy, distribute, modify, and create derivative works for non-commercial purposes, provided that you:
- keep the original copyright notice, license link, and project source (e.g., “Source: flyMD – https://github.com/flyhunterl/flymd”);
- clearly indicate any changes you make (what/when/who) and do not imply endorsement by the original author;
- include this license text with any redistribution; and
- comply with third-party licenses included in this project.

2. Non-Commercial vs. Commercial
Non-Commercial: personal study/research, non-profit education/academia, or internal non-profit demos.
Commercial: any activity for commercial gain or value, including but not limited to selling the software, providing paid/monetized services (ads, subscription, value-added), using in enterprise production (including SaaS/cloud/hosted services), or delivering for commercial projects. Commercial use requires prior written authorization from the copyright holder (flyhunterl <flyhunterl@gmail.com>).

3. Restrictions
Do not remove/hide/alter copyright, trademark, source link, or license notice. Do not use the software illegally or to infringe others’ rights. Do not circumvent security/compliance measures.

4. Disclaimer
Provided “as is”, without any warranty. To the maximum extent permitted by law, the authors/contributors are not liable for any damages arising from use, inability to use, or distribution of the software.

5. Termination
Any breach terminates your rights automatically; you must cease use and destroy copies. Non-breaching downstream recipients remain bound by this license.

6. Third-Party Components
Third-party components remain under their respective licenses (e.g., MIT/Apache-2.0/BSD-3-Clause). See THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md.

